<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,801,1044]" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,801,828]" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">Diagnosis</emphasis>
(after 
<bibRefCitation author="Schuh, R. T. &amp; Weirauch, C. &amp; Grillo, H." box="[341,543,801,828]" pageId="1" pageNumber="383" pagination="1 - 43" refId="ref3367" refString="Schuh, R. T., Weirauch, C. &amp; Grillo, H. (2015) Revision of Aphelonotus Uhler (Hemiptera: Heteroptera: Pachynomidae), with description of six new species and documentation of nymphal morphology for three species. American Museum Novitates, 3829, 1 - 43. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 3829.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Schuh 
<emphasis box="[418,475,801,827]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
). Body of moderate size (body length from anterior margin of pronotal collar to apex of membrane 
<quantity box="[369,537,837,864]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.105" metricValueMax="3.46" metricValueMin="2.75" pageId="1" pageNumber="383" unit="mm" value="3.105" valueMax="3.46" valueMin="2.75">2.75–3.46 mm</quantity>
); head moderately elongate; eyes globular (
<figureCitation box="[1031,1101,837,863]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1835,1860]" captionTargetBox="[214,1356,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[214,1373,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Morphology of Aphelonotus schuhi sp. nov., male holotype. 3—body in dorsal view (magnification 37×); 4—head and thorax, dorsal view (70×); 5—clavus and base of corium (150×); 6—protibia, inner view (180×); 7—genital capsule with parameres in rest position, dorsal view (200×); 8—detached left paramere, anterior view (500×); 9—right paramere articulated to genital capsule in rest position, dorsal view (500×). Abbreviations: ia—inner angle, p—protuberance between shaft and blade, s—paramere shaft, sas—subapical spine. Scale bars: 3–4—0.5 mm, 5–7—0.2 mm, 8–9—0.05 mm. (ESEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); endocorium shortened (rendering medial fracture very short); corium smooth (
<figureCitation box="[734,803,873,900]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1835,1860]" captionTargetBox="[214,1356,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[214,1373,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Morphology of Aphelonotus schuhi sp. nov., male holotype. 3—body in dorsal view (magnification 37×); 4—head and thorax, dorsal view (70×); 5—clavus and base of corium (150×); 6—protibia, inner view (180×); 7—genital capsule with parameres in rest position, dorsal view (200×); 8—detached left paramere, anterior view (500×); 9—right paramere articulated to genital capsule in rest position, dorsal view (500×). Abbreviations: ia—inner angle, p—protuberance between shaft and blade, s—paramere shaft, sas—subapical spine. Scale bars: 3–4—0.5 mm, 5–7—0.2 mm, 8–9—0.05 mm. (ESEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); membrane without cells (
<figureCitation box="[1113,1185,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–2" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1941,1966]" captionTargetBox="[187,1400,866,1897]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1436,813,1916]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–2. Habitus of Aphelonotus schuhi sp. nov., male holotype. 1—dorsal view, 2—ventral view. (Photographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698733" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698733/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">Figs 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1200,1215,873,899]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1835,1860]" captionTargetBox="[214,1356,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[214,1373,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Morphology of Aphelonotus schuhi sp. nov., male holotype. 3—body in dorsal view (magnification 37×); 4—head and thorax, dorsal view (70×); 5—clavus and base of corium (150×); 6—protibia, inner view (180×); 7—genital capsule with parameres in rest position, dorsal view (200×); 8—detached left paramere, anterior view (500×); 9—right paramere articulated to genital capsule in rest position, dorsal view (500×). Abbreviations: ia—inner angle, p—protuberance between shaft and blade, s—paramere shaft, sas—subapical spine. Scale bars: 3–4—0.5 mm, 5–7—0.2 mm, 8–9—0.05 mm. (ESEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">3</figureCitation>
); ventral surface of protibia flattened, provided with an anterior row of stout and moderately elongate spines (
<figureCitation box="[1155,1223,909,936]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1835,1860]" captionTargetBox="[214,1356,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[214,1373,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Morphology of Aphelonotus schuhi sp. nov., male holotype. 3—body in dorsal view (magnification 37×); 4—head and thorax, dorsal view (70×); 5—clavus and base of corium (150×); 6—protibia, inner view (180×); 7—genital capsule with parameres in rest position, dorsal view (200×); 8—detached left paramere, anterior view (500×); 9—right paramere articulated to genital capsule in rest position, dorsal view (500×). Abbreviations: ia—inner angle, p—protuberance between shaft and blade, s—paramere shaft, sas—subapical spine. Scale bars: 3–4—0.5 mm, 5–7—0.2 mm, 8–9—0.05 mm. (ESEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
); paramere slender and sinuous (
<figureCitation box="[299,401,945,971]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1835,1860]" captionTargetBox="[214,1356,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[214,1373,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Morphology of Aphelonotus schuhi sp. nov., male holotype. 3—body in dorsal view (magnification 37×); 4—head and thorax, dorsal view (70×); 5—clavus and base of corium (150×); 6—protibia, inner view (180×); 7—genital capsule with parameres in rest position, dorsal view (200×); 8—detached left paramere, anterior view (500×); 9—right paramere articulated to genital capsule in rest position, dorsal view (500×). Abbreviations: ia—inner angle, p—protuberance between shaft and blade, s—paramere shaft, sas—subapical spine. Scale bars: 3–4—0.5 mm, 5–7—0.2 mm, 8–9—0.05 mm. (ESEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">Figs 7–9</figureCitation>
), oriented subparallelly in rest (
<figureCitation box="[756,824,945,972]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–9" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1835,1860]" captionTargetBox="[214,1356,181,1810]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[214,1373,181,1810]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 3–9. Morphology of Aphelonotus schuhi sp. nov., male holotype. 3—body in dorsal view (magnification 37×); 4—head and thorax, dorsal view (70×); 5—clavus and base of corium (150×); 6—protibia, inner view (180×); 7—genital capsule with parameres in rest position, dorsal view (200×); 8—detached left paramere, anterior view (500×); 9—right paramere articulated to genital capsule in rest position, dorsal view (500×). Abbreviations: ia—inner angle, p—protuberance between shaft and blade, s—paramere shaft, sas—subapical spine. Scale bars: 3–4—0.5 mm, 5–7—0.2 mm, 8–9—0.05 mm. (ESEM micrographs: P. Kment)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3698735" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3698735/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="383">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
